        <summary type="html"><![CDATA[<p><strong>Thirty-Six</strong></p>
<p>Today I stand where circles meet,
Where numbered years and heartbeats greet;
Not merely older—more aware,
Of hidden patterns everywhere.</p>
<p>For life first learned to write in <strong>three</strong>,
Its secret script of destiny;
Each tiny codon, softly spun,
A whispered verse: <em>Become. Be one.</em></p>
<p>And from the humble number <strong>six</strong>
Rose carbon&rsquo;s quiet, ancient bricks;
Six steadfast sparks in every flame,
The dust of stars from which we came.</p>]]></summary>
